# Open Questions Check

## The Rule

Before implementing code that depends on an unresolved design decision, confirm [MANIFEST.md §11.1](../../MANIFEST.md#111-foundation-milestone-complete) (no blocking questions before Phase 2) and that the choice is recorded in the relevant `docs/` spec and [changelog](../../MANIFEST.md#changelog) if it is a new fork.

All foundation and Phase 2 blocking decisions are **resolved**. The remaining open items are Phase 3 scope:

## All Decisions Resolved Through Phase 3

There are no remaining open questions before Phase 3 implementation. The 4 Phase 3 items were resolved:

| # | Decision | Outcome |
|---|----------|---------|
| 1 | Image/video optimization | `loading="lazy"` on all `<img>` and `<video>` — client-side, no proxy |
| 2 | State persistence | No persistence — every refresh starts fresh |
| 3 | `parameterPanel` schema | Custom Lastriko typed object only (no Zod) |
| 4 | Multi-page support | Deferred — `ui.tabs()` covers the use case |

## All Foundation + Phase 2 Decisions — Locked

These are **resolved** and must not be re-opened without updating MANIFEST.md:

| Decision | Resolution |
|----------|-----------|
| Execution model | `app()` once per connection; button callbacks; handles |
| Wire format | `FRAGMENT` messages (HTML); `outerHTML` swap on client |
| State | Nanostores server-side only; `ConnectionScope` per connection |
| Layout | `shell()` + `grid()` — no standalone `sidebar()`, no `columns()` |
| CSS | Self-contained `lastriko.css`; no Pico.css; no CDN |
| Client rendering | `outerHTML` swap; no diffing library; no framework |
| Plugin isolation | `plugin → core` only |
| streamText | Handle-based; `.append(chunk)` + `STREAM_CHUNK`; no re-run |
| table | `TableHandle` with `.prepend/.append/.remove/.onRowClick`; `RowHandle.update()` |
| metric | `MetricHandle`; value is always `string`; `.update(value, opts?)` |
| text | `TextHandle`; `.update(content)` pushes `FRAGMENT` |
| Hot reload | Through Phase 2: full reset. Phase 3+: `hotReloadPreserve: true` (default) preserves inputs, scroll, active tabs |
| Button lock | `btn.setLoading(true/false)` |

## How to Resolve a Question

1. Make a decision
2. Add a row to the MANIFEST.md [changelog](../../MANIFEST.md#changelog) and update the relevant spec in `docs/`
3. Update the relevant component spec doc
4. Update MANIFEST.md changelog
5. Commit manifesto update separately from the code change
